CSS Form Formating

setting width for input
-use the width property to determine the width of input field:
    input{

        width:100;
    }


Use attribute selectors to style specific input style
-input[type=text] - will only select text fields
-input[type=password] -wll only select password fields
-input[type=number] - will only select number fields

Padding and margin with inputs
-use the padding and margin property to add space inside(padding)and outside(margin) the text field;

<style>
    input[type=text]{

        width:100%;
        padding:15px 20px;
        margin:8px 0;

    }


</style>

Bordered Inputs
-Use the border property to change

Focused Inputs
Use the :focus selector to do something with the input